42821"}, {"#name": "pixel-height", "_": "582"}, {"#name": "pixel-width", "_": "1333"}, {"#name": "attachment-type", "_": "IMAGE-HIGH-RES"}]}]}, {"#name": "abstract", "$": {"class": "author", "id": "d1e1709", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "d1e1710"}, "_": "Abstract"}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "d1e1712", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "d1e1713", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "__text__", "_": "Large numbers of maintenance Work Request Notification (WRN) records are created by industry as part of standard business work flows. These digital records hold invaluable insights crucial to best practice in asset management. Of particular interest are the cause\u2013effect relations in the "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "long text"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " WRN field. In this research we develop a two-stage deep learning pipeline to extract cause-and-effect triples and construct a causal graph database. A novel sentence-level noise removal method in the first stage filters out information extraneous to causal semantics. The second stage leverages a joint entity-and-relation extraction model to extract causal relations. To train the noise removal and causality extraction models we produced an annotated dataset of 1027 WRN records. The results for causality extraction as measured by F1-score are 83% and 92% for the identification of "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "Cause"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " and "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "Effect"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " entities respectively, and 78% for a correct causal relation between these entities. The pipeline is applied to a real-word, industrial plant dataset of 98,000 WRN records to produce a graph database. This work provides a framework for technical personnel to query the causes of equipment failures enabling answers to questions such as \u201cwhat are the most "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "common"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": ", "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "costly"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": ", and "}, {"#name": "italic", "_": "recent"}, {"#name": "__text__", "_": " causes of failures at my facility?\u201d."}]}]}]}, {"#name": "abstract", "$": {"class": "graphical", "id": "d1e1734", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "d1e1735"}, "_": "Graphical abstract"}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "d1e1737", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "d1e1738", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "display", "$$": [{"#name": "figure", "$": {"id": "dfig1"}, "$$": [{"#name": "link", "$": {"xmlns:xlink": true, "id": "d1e1742", "locator": "ga1", "href": "pii:S0166361524000381/ga1", "role": "http://data.elsevier.com/vocabulary/ElsevierContentTypes/23.4"}}]}]}]}]}]}, {"#name": "abstract", "$": {"class": "author-highlights", "id": "d1e1743", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "section-title", "$": {"id": "d1e1744"}, "_": "Highlights"}, {"#name": "abstract-sec", "$": {"id": "d1e1746", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "simple-para", "$": {"id": "d1e1747", "view": "all"}, "$$": [{"#name": "list", "$": {"id": "d1e1749"}, "$$": [{"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "d1e1750"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "d1e1753", "view": "all"}, "_": "Free-text maintenance work request documents hold valuable causal information on asset failures."}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "d1e1755"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "d1e1758", "view": "all"}, "_": "Work requests are multi-sentence and contain information extraneous to causal analysis so a novel sentence-level noise removal method is employed to remove unnecessary information."}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "d1e1760"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "d1e1763", "view": "all"}, "_": "SpERT, an attention model for span-based joint entity and relation extraction is used to produce causal triples."}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "d1e1765"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "d1e1768", "view": "all"}, "_": "We demonstrate the pipeline on a real industrial data set of 98,000 work requests to build a causal graph database."}]}, {"#name": "list-item", "$": {"id": "d1e1770"}, "$$": [{"#name": "label", "_": "\u2022"}, {"#name": "para", "$": {"id": "d1e1773", "view": "all"}, "_": "Graph queries are used to address questions of value to reliability engineers."}]}]}]}]}]}]}}